<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 5:49PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL ELK...SOUTHWESTERN
POTTER AND NORTHERN CAMERON COUNTIES THROUGH 615 PM EDT...
At 549 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles east of St. Marys, moving southwest at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cameron, Wharton, Emporium, Truman, Sizerville and Hicks Run.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
